    h2 Sheet Modal Slots
    p `<f7-sheet>` component has additional slots for custom elements:
    ul
      li `default` - element will be inserted as a child of scrollable `<div class="sheet-modal-inner">` element
      li `static` - same as `default`
      li `fixed` - element will be inserted before the scrollable `<div class="sheet-modal-inner">` element

    ```html
      <f7-sheet>
        <template #fixed>
          <span>Fixed slot</span>
        </template>
        <template #static>
          <span>Static slot</span>
        </template>
        <span>Default slot</span>
      </f7-sheet>
    ```
    p Renders to
    ```html
      <div class="sheet-modal">
        <span>Fixed slot</span>
        <div class="sheet-modal-inner">
          <span>Default slot</span>
          <span>Static slot</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    ```

    h2 Sheet Modal v-model
    p Sheet Modal component supports `v-model` on `opened` prop:
    ```html
      <template>
        <f7-page>
          <f7-sheet v-model:opened="isOpened">
            ...
          </f7-sheet>
          <p>Modal is opened: {{ isOpened }}</p>
        </f7-page>
      </template>
      <script>
        export default {
          data() {
            return {
              isOpened: false,
            };
          }
        };
      </script>
    ```

    h2 Open And Close Sheet Modal
    p You can control Sheet Modal state, open and closing it:
    ul
      li using its <a href="../docs/sheet-modal.html">Sheet Modal API</a>
      li by passing `true` or `false` to its `opened` prop
      li by clicking on <a href="link.html">Link</a> or <a href="button.html">Button</a> with relevant `sheet-open` property (to open it) and `sheet-close` property to close it

